fr.zelus.jarvis.recognition

Class DefaultIntentRecognitionProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.zelus.jarvis.recognition.DefaultIntentRecognitionProvider
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IntentRecognitionProvider

    public class DefaultIntentRecognitionProvider
extends Object
implements IntentRecognitionProvider
    A default IntentRecognitionProvider that manages JarvisSessions.

    This class does not implement any IntentDefinition-related method, and throws UnsupportedOperationExceptions when calling them. DefaultIntentRecognitionProvider should be used when the created bot does not require any RecognizedIntent computation, and only requires session management. This is for example the case for event-driven bots that only forward received events to a given output.

    The DefaultIntentRecognitionProvider will be used by jarvis if the application's Configuration file does not contain specific IntentRecognitionProvider properties (see IntentRecognitionProviderFactory.getIntentRecognitionProvider(JarvisCore, Configuration)).

    See Also:
    UnsupportedOperationException, IntentRecognitionProviderFactory
